item.description:
Add / edit attribute valueWhile adding or editing an attribute value, the following fields / toggles / parameters are displayed:
Attribute group This drop-down lists all the attributes and is mandatory. In the case of multistore, it lists only the attributes associated with the store(s) selected as context. When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Choose the attribute group for this value.&rdquo;
Value This field is mandatory and can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed.

Add / Edit tagWhile adding or editing tag, the following fields/drop downs/parameters are displayed:
Name This field allows to fill the name of the tag and is mandatory. If the save button is pressed and if this field is empty, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The name field is required.&rdquo;
Language This drop-down menu allows selecting the language of the tag and is mandatory. The default country (selected in International &gt; Localization &gt; Configuration) is selected by default.

In this page the customer details are input.
Customer Social title Can be selected: &ldquo;Mr.&rdquo; or &ldquo;Mrs.&rdquo;
First name This field is mandatory, when trying to save with the field empty, will show a message: &ldquo;please fill out this field.&rdquo;. Below has a help text: &ldquo;Only letters and the dot (.) character, followed by a space, are allowed.&rdquo;. When trying to save with invalid characters entered, will show an error: &ldquo;The &ldquo;First name&rdquo; field is invalid.

SPECIFICATIONS - DESIGN &gt; THEME &amp; LOGO &gt; THEME &amp; LOGOAs a merchant, I want to be able to set up my store&rsquo;s look.
The page can have extra sections if:
several themes are installed;
the multistore feature is enabled;
RTL languages are enabled;
the MBO module is installed. HeaderThere are 4 buttons:
&lsquo;Add new theme&rsquo; button redirects to the Design &gt; Theme &amp; Logo &gt; Add new theme page.

SPECIFICATIONS - ADVANCED PARAMETERS &gt; WEBSERVICEThe listing page is composed of the list of the webservice keys and the configuration section.
Webservice Add new webserviceA button &ldquo;Add new webservice&rdquo; allows to create a new webservice key and redirects to the add page.
Information messageAn information message is displayed: &ldquo;It is preferable to use SSL (https:) for webservice calls, as it avoids the &ldquo;man in the middle&rdquo; type security issues.&rdquo;
